  "prompt": "How do I recover my Facebook account password without a recovery email or phone number?",
  "response": "Recovering your Facebook account password without a recovery email or phone number can be challenging, but there are steps you can take to try to regain access:\n\n1. **Identify Friends Feature**:\n   - Go to the Facebook login page.\n   - Click on \"Forgot password?\".\n   - Enter your username, email, or phone number associated with your account.\n   - If you see a list of accounts, select yours. Facebook will show recovery options; since you don't have access to your email or phone number, look for \"No longer have access to these?\" or similar options.\n   - Follow the instructions provided. Facebook might let you choose trusted contacts.\n\n2. **Trusted Contacts**:\n   - If you have set up trusted contacts, you can use them to recover your account.\n   - Click \"Reveal my trusted contacts\" and ask your trusted friends for the codes that Facebook sends them.\n   - Enter those codes to retrieve access to your account.\n\n3. **Facebook Help Center**:\n   - Visit the Facebook Help Center at https://www.facebook.com/help/.\n   - Search for account recovery options and follow the instructions provided.\n   - You may need to submit a request for help and provide identification proof to verify your identity.\n\n4. **Identity Verification**:\n   - Facebook might ask for a government-issued ID or similar proof of identity.\n   - Follow the steps to submit your ID. Your account will be reviewed, and if verified, you might regain access.\n\n5. **Old Passwords**:\n   - If you remember any old passwords you've used for your account, try using them. Sometimes, entering old passwords can prompt additional recovery options.\n\n6. **Account Recovery**:\n   - If all else fails, create a new account and reach out to Facebook support through the new account.\n   - Provide detailed information about your old account and follow their guidance.\n\nRemember to frequently check your email and any messages from Facebook regarding your recovery request. Be patient, as account recovery might take some time.",
